Feet placement: Your feet should be shoulder-width apart, with your toes pointing slightly outward.

Posture: Stand tall with your chest up, shoulders back and down, and your core engaged.

Depth: Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as close as you can get without discomfort or pain. Keep your knees in line with your toes.

Weight distribution: Your weight should be evenly distributed through your feet and heels.

Hip movement: As you squat down, push your hips back and down, keeping your knees behind your toes.

Breathing: Inhale as you lower your body, and exhale as you push back up.

Spinal alignment: Keep your spine in a neutral position, without rounding or arching your back.

Bar placement: If you are using a barbell, place it on your upper back, not on your neck.
